title: NCAA SPORTS ROUNDUP: Folke places second, leads Murray State at Banister
content:
GLENCOE, Ala. — The Murray State women’s golf team bought home a fourth-place showing and Moa Folke was the runner-up Tuesday at the Chris Banister Golf Classic. The three-day event hosted by Jacksonville State wrapped up Tuesday at Silver Lakes Golf Club. 
  
The Racers fired rounds of 308-313-306—927 and finished between the two Ohio Valley Conference squads they often battle, Morehead State (925) and Jacksonville State (929). Troy was the winner at 921.
